<tt>Wed Feb 19 14:00:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was in the 23rd TASS, a Nail FAC in O-1s, when the first Nimrod A-26s appeared.  In fact I have two or three jump-seat area orientation missions in my Form 5.  I have written an unpublished book about my 1966 experience, that necessarily mentions many personalities and incidents form that crazy year, from Col &quot;Farney Barmer&quot; down to the night an A-26 crashed in a thunderstorm and the day one of our best guys was shot down riding the jump seat on one of those orientation rides in Harley's Valley (so named after my once best friend Lee Harley, with whom I flew many missions in pairs.  He was shot down while I was in Bangkok).<br><br>
Years later (1972) I went back in KC-135s.  People told me I wouldn't recognize NKP, but I never got there to see.  Of course we talked to INVERT on nearly every mission.  I'd like to know more about the trail and what happened there after 1966.  Are you putting together accounts?<br><br>

